delete.description:
Mirror of AddEntitiesToGroup: per-entity revision checks
surface mismatches as per-entity failures, not whole-request 409.

## Body
```json
{
  "entities": [
    { "entityId": 349, "revision": 5 },
    { "entityId": 350, "revision": 7 }
  ]
}
```

get.description:
This endpoint reconciles both MySQL-based global DNT rules and untracked identities from PostgreSQL.
## Filtering
- **term**: single search string (case-insensitive, partial match). When set, matches username **or** logon domain on each row; for identity rows, also associated user **display id** and **email** values. **term** takes precedence over **username** and **domain** (those are ignored when **term** is non-empty).
- **username**: filter by username (case-insensitive, partial match)
- **domain**: filter by domain or logon domain
- **filter=all** (default): return all entries  
- **filter=associatedUser**: only entries tied to existing identities (source = identity)  
- **filter=global**: only MySQL DNT rules not linked to an identity (source = global)
- Example: `&filter=associatedUser`
## Sorting
- **sortOn=username** (default)
- **sortOn=logondomain**
- **sortOn=associatedUser**
- **sort=asc** or **sort=desc**
- Example: `sortOn=username&sort=asc`
## Pagination
- **pageSize**: number of entries per page (default 50)
- **page**: page number to retrieve (starting from 1)
- Example: `pageSize=100&page=2`
## Full Request Example
- `/identity/v1/dnt?&filter=all&sortOn=username&sort=asc&pageSize=10&page=2`

